<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1944-09-03T23:54:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1944-09-03T23:54:00-05:00" n="799" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d799">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">890F.24/9–444: Telegram</note>
                            <head>
                                <hi rend="italic">The Appointed Minister to Saudi Arabia</hi>
                                    (<persName type="from"><hi rend="italic">Eddy</hi></persName>)
                                    <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                                        State</gloss>
                                </hi>
                            </head>
                            <opener>
                                <dateline rendition="#right">
                                    <placeName>
                                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Jidda</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1944-09-04T08:00:00+03:06">September 4, 1944—8 a.m.</date>
                                    <lb/> [Received 4:47 p.m.]</dateline>
                            </opener>
                            <p>264. Jordan told me today: <list>
                                    <label>1.</label>
                                    <item>Highly qualified Indian Muslim already selected and
                                        available for financial adviser to King whenever our two
                                        Governments agree.</item>
                                    <label>2.</label>
                                    <item>British Military Mission at Taif being reinforced by
                                        mobile repair units and 22 personnel.</item>
                                    <label>3.</label>
                                    <item>Eastern Bank has requested Saudi Government for permission
                                        to open branch in Saudi Arabia on Persian Gulf, obviously a
                                        move to match National City Bank.<note n="44" xml:id="d799fn44">The National City Bank of New York had
                                            requested permission from the Saudi Arabian Government
                                            to open a branch at Ras Tanura.</note>
                                    </item>
                                    <label>4.</label>
                                    <item>He rejects proposal to explain budget to Saudi officials.
                                        (See Department’s 166, August 23, 9 p.m.<note n="43" xml:id="d799fn43">See footnote 39, <ref target="#pg_730">p. 730</ref>.</note>)</item>
                                    <label>5.</label>
                                    <item>He proposes MESC plan to supervise food reserves in
                                        controlled warehouses.</item>
                                    <label>6.</label>
                                    <item>He declines to leave statement of present food reserves
                                        and overall needs to MESC Jidda, claiming they lack
                                        experience and facts.</item>
                                </list>
                            </p>
                            <pb facs="0745" n="733" xml:id="pg_733"/>
                            <p>MESC conference in Jidda this week will be crucial in determining
                                Jordan’s ability to dominate MESC British personnel and in arriving
                                at satisfactory supply program.</p>
                            <p>Details by pouch.<note n="45" xml:id="d799fn45">Despatch 4, September
                                    5, not printed.</note>
                            </p>
                            <closer>
                                <signed>
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Eddy</hi>
                                </signed>
                            </closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>